.TH "__bitmap_shift_right" 9 "__bitmap_shift_right" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__bitmap_shift_right \- logical right shift of the bits in a bitmap
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" __bitmap_shift_right
.BI "(unsigned long *dst "  ","
.BI "const unsigned long *src "  ","
.BI "unsigned shift "  ","
.BI "unsigned nbits "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dst" 12
destination bitmap
.IP "src" 12
source bitmap
.IP "shift" 12
shift by this many bits
.IP "nbits" 12
bitmap size, in bits
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Shifting right (dividing) means moving bits in the MS -> LS bit
direction.  Zeros are fed into the vacated MS positions and the
LS bits shifted off the bottom are lost.
